		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://mobile-accessibility.idrc.ocadu.ca/archives/396" />
		<id>http://scyp.idrc.ocad.ca/?p=396</id>
		<updated>2009-11-17T21:00:21Z</updated>
		<published>2009-11-17T20:54:18Z</published>
		<category scheme="https://mobile-accessibility.idrc.ocadu.ca" term="Uncategorized" />		<summary type="html"><![CDATA[Naomi Justason, an Occupational Therapy student who completed her research with SCYP last year, was announced as the 2008-2009 recipient of the Pearl Gryfe assistive technology award. Sponsored by Assistive Technology Clinic, this award is presented by the Department of Occupational Science &#38; Occupational Therapy at the University of Toronto &#8220;to the student who has [&#8230;]]]></summary>
		<content type="html" xml:base="https://mobile-accessibility.idrc.ocadu.ca/archives/396"><![CDATA[<p>Naomi Justason, an Occupational Therapy student who completed her research with SCYP last year, was announced as the 2008-2009 recipient of the Pearl Gryfe assistive technology award. Sponsored by Assistive Technology Clinic, this award is presented by the <a href="http://www.ot.utoronto.ca/">Department of Occupational Science &amp; Occupational Therapy at the University of Toronto</a> &#8220;to the student who has demonstrated a keen interest in and excellent understanding of the role assistive technology plays in improving the functional independence of people with various disabilities&#8221;.</p>
<p>Naomi obtained this award for her research entitled: &#8220;GPS-based navigation in the everyday life of blind users&#8221;. A copy of the poster she presented at the <a href="http://www.ot.utoronto.ca/research/research_day/">Thelma Cardwell Research Day</a> is available from the following link:</p>
<p><a href="http://scyp.idrc.ocad.ca/media/slides/OT-GPS-poster.pdf">http://scyp.idrc.ocad.ca/media/slides/OT-GPS-poster.pdf</a></p>
<p>Congratulations Naomi!</p>
