		<title type="html"><![CDATA[SCYP Re-loaded]]></title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://mobile-accessibility.idrc.ocadu.ca/archives/303" />
		<id>http://scyp.idrc.ocad.ca/?p=303</id>
		<updated>2009-10-22T03:01:33Z</updated>
		<published>2009-10-22T03:01:33Z</published>
		<category scheme="https://mobile-accessibility.idrc.ocadu.ca" term="Uncategorized" />		<summary type="html"><![CDATA[It has been a while since the last time we wrote a blog entry, but now is as good a time as any to finally do it. We do have lots of good news to share though; for starters, the SCYP website has been completely revamped to reflect our current activities and to make it [&#8230;]]]></summary>
		<content type="html" xml:base="https://mobile-accessibility.idrc.ocadu.ca/archives/303"><![CDATA[<p>It has been a while since the last time we wrote a blog entry, but now is as good a time as any to finally do it. We do have lots of good news to share though; for starters, the SCYP website has been completely revamped to reflect our current activities and to make it more consistent with the look &#038; feel of the <a href="http://idrc.ocad.ca/">ATRC site</a>.</p>
<p>We also released a week ago a new version of the <a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/13227">tagin! Firefox extension</a> which, amongst other minor improvements, included a change of server location. So, if you have previous versions installed, you will really want to upgrade because we broke all the previous versions!</p>
<p>The new academic year also brought a bunch of outstanding students working on various SCYP projects, like Julie and Esther from the Occupational Therapy department, as well as Tian, Mark and Jingqi from Computer Science and Engineering. They will be working on everything from a documentary narrating the struggle for access to assistive technology by people with disabilities in the GTA, to a bluetooth link that allows powered-wheelchair users to control a mobile device from their wheelchair. So we will be blogging away in the near future to show off their achievements!</p>
]]></content>
