		<title type="html"><![CDATA[Printed circuit boards anyone?]]></title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://mobile-accessibility.idrc.ocadu.ca/archives/21" />
		<id>http://localhost/wordpress/?p=21</id>
		<updated>2009-03-21T00:21:58Z</updated>
		<published>2008-09-10T18:33:00Z</published>
		<category scheme="https://mobile-accessibility.idrc.ocadu.ca" term="Uncategorized" /><category scheme="https://mobile-accessibility.idrc.ocadu.ca" term="CAD" /><category scheme="https://mobile-accessibility.idrc.ocadu.ca" term="PCB" />		<summary type="html"><![CDATA[We would like to extend our appreciation to the Department of Electrical &#38; Computer Engineering at the University of Toronto and Cadence Design Systems since they have made available to us a handful of licenses for industry-quality printed circuit board (PCB) computer-aided design (CAD) software. The software will be available to UofT students working with [&#8230;]]]></summary>
		<content type="html" xml:base="https://mobile-accessibility.idrc.ocadu.ca/archives/21"><![CDATA[<p><a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/65/PCB_Spectrum.jpg"><img style="margin: 0pt 10px 10px 0pt; float: left; cursor: pointer; width: 220px; height: 114px;" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/65/PCB_Spectrum.jpg" alt="printed circuit" border="0" /></a>We would like to extend our appreciation to the <a href="http://www.ece.utoronto.ca/">Department of Electrical &amp; Computer Engineering</a> at the University of Toronto and <a href="http://www.cadence.com/">Cadence Design Systems</a> since they have made available to us a handful of licenses for industry-quality printed circuit board (PCB) computer-aided design (CAD) software.</p>
<p>The software will be available to UofT students working with SCYP at the <a href="http://idrc.ocad.ca/">ATRC</a> and will be most useful in the completion of our current <a href="http://wiki.scyp.idrc.ocad.ca/wiki/AlternativeInput">alternative input projects</a>. Special thanks to Jaro Pristupa for helping us provide the best available resources to our students!</p>
